Package: pdn-bpqchat
Version: @VERSION@
Architecture: @ARCH@
Maintainer: Tom Fanning <tom@m0lte.uk>
Recommends: packetnet
Section: hamradio
Priority: optional
Homepage: https://github.com/m0lte/pdn-bpqchat
Description: BPQ-Chat-compatible chat node app package for the Packet.NET node (pdn)
 A BPQ-Chat-compatible chat node — multi-user chat for RF and web users that
 peers with the BPQ Chat network. Ships as a Packet.NET app PACKAGE: pdn
 discovers it under /usr/share/packetnet/apps/bpqchat and the node owner enables
 it from the control panel (default off). A single static Go binary — no runtime
 or shared-library dependencies. Inert without the packetnet node host (hence the
 soft Recommends), but installable standalone.
